The paper deals with the performance analysis of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The analysis is focused on the effects of channel degradations, which are related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system design (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of orthogonal space-time block codes, which is a technique in multimedia communication (cs.MM). Finally, the paper presents results on the capacity of MIMO systems, which is a topic in communication networks (cs.COM).
